article.headline: VCU 82, Georgia St. 69
article.story: ATLANTA -- Joey Rodriguez scored 21 points, leading Virginia Commonwealth in an 82-69 win over Georgia State on Saturday. Jamie Skeen added 16 points and Bradford Burgess had 14 for the Rams (12-4, 4-3 Colonial Athletic Association), who have won three straight. Larry Sanders grabbed 11 rebounds and blocked a shot. Burgess went 4-for-5 from beyond the arc for the Rams. Trae Goldston's 3-pointer put Georgia State up 32-28 with 6:40 left before halftime, but the Rams put together an 18-6 run the rest of the period to lead at the break. They never trailed again, outscoring the Panthers 36-31 in the second. Goldston, who hit three 3s and was 4-for-4 at the foul line, finished with 19 points and six steals for the Panthers (8-11, 2-5). Georgia State has lost five in a row. The Panthers lost despite turning the ball over just nine times and outscoring VCU 19-10 on the fastbreak.
